\n<Chelsea>You've grown so much♥ But remember, if you do something bad,
big sis will come to punish you!

\n<Chelsea>Next time, let's share our adventure stories! I'll tell you
all about my adventures too. But that'll be way in the
future, so wait for it!

\n<Chelsea>Rui, you're short but you have big boobs. Just like my
little sibling should. All the women in the Catfield family
are like that.

\n<Chelsea>Rui, are you working hard at your studies? Sorry, it seems
like I'm the only one who gets to be free. Both of us have
expectations to live up to...

\n<Chelsea>The Cat Borrower's hand is said to be the hand of our
ancestors! It's amazing that they lend us a hand from the
other world. Rui, you had mom's hand, right?

\n<Chelsea>So whose hand is the Luisham? I don't know, maybe grandma's?
I heard grandma was also a beauty.

\n<Chelsea>Then whose hand is the Wanzworth? I don't know, maybe
grandma's? I heard grandma was also a beauty.

\n<Chelsea>I wonder if the day will come when we'll fight together.
Well, I think I'll probably win by a landslide. It'd be
pitiful to beat you up too badly.

\n<Chelsea>The Cat Borrower's hand is a secret technique passed down
through the Catfield family. I couldn't use it at all and I
don't have magical power, but I do have physical strength.
Whatever that means.

\n<Chelsea>I'm adventuring with a hero after all sorts of things! Shion
is really delicate and unreliable, but strong! That's why
I'm sticking with him. I want to win someday!

\n<Chelsea>Have you cleared Challenge Mode? You only get a small
weapon, but it's fun to fight with a handicap!

\n<Chelsea>Is grandpa doing well? I heard he used to be quite strong.
Apparently, he had a completely new fighting style that
combined swordsmanship and boomerangs.

\n<Chelsea>It must have been tough fighting succubi since they're
always doing lewd things, right? When your dick gets hard,
it seems like it would be hard to move.

\n<Chelsea>This room is called an "ikuukan?" or also a "clear bay."
What the heck is that!

I haven't seen Ending 2 yet... To achieve it, your karma
must be at its maximum (by not making any wrong choices). To
save Meere.
Would you like to see a hint?

To save Meere, you will need a "White Vial". You can obtain
the White Vial during the "Battle of Bijou-1" by "not
hitting the treasure chest even once".

To use the White Vial, you must know what's inside. You can
learn how to use it by "reading a book" during the
investigation of the ancient ruins in "Bijou-1".

If you "have the White Vial" and "know how to use it", you
can save Meere by "defeating Meere in the second battle and
resisting the temptation".
カルマを最大にする方法

The basic rule is not to succumb to temptation. You must
defeat the succubus. However, for "Ladro's second battle"
alone, succumbing to temptation is the correct answer. (The
text will also turn blue.)

If you cut down Meere, your karma will still increase, but
you will no longer meet the conditions for the ending.

Ending 2 "Phantom Thieves Kittens". Karma is at its highest
state. Cleared by saving Meere.

The slums were half-destroyed, but we succeeded in repelling
the monsters. The cat's paw is no longer usable, but we
should be fine without borrowing anyone's help now.

However, taught by Radlo to have sticky fingers, the Kittens
continue to steal for the sake of the children in the
orphanage today. Until the day Dreene and Lumare can join
hands.
\n<Moo>What business do you have with me?

\n<Moo>I do enjoy a good chat. Go ahead and ask. I know everything.
Some even call me a walking library. That's a lie, though.

\n<Moo>Coagulation crystals were born long ago during a conflict
known as the Elemental War, a crystallization of "blood,
malice, and hatred" that naturally solidified. Most of them
have been obtained by the Demon King or already disposed of
by humans.

\n<Moo>However, like the turmoil this time, there's a chance some
were sealed away and hidden, or remain in places no one can
find. We must find and dispose of them before the demons do.

\n<Moo>Malice is the emotion that monsters favor most and is also
the source of their existence. That's why they attack
humans. Simple, isn't it?

\n<Moo>In ancient times, humans were broadly divided into four
types: the Fire Folk, the Water Folk, the Wind Folk, and the
Thunder Folk. Their conflict was known as the Elemental War.

\n<Moo>You have inherited a strong lineage of both Fire and Wind
Folk. The mixing of attributes is also a result of mutual
acceptance.

\n<Moo>You seem to be able to use magic of different attributes
with ease, but normally that would be incredibly difficult.
Only a few geniuses and heroes can perform such feats.

\n<Moo>To put it simply, it's about whether your ancestors were
apes or something else. And hybrids between beastfolk and
humans often turn out human. If interbreeding continues, the
number of beastfolk will likely decrease.

\n<Moo>The Catfield family has been uniting beastfolk partly to
prevent their numbers from dwindling too much. You all
understand this best.

\n<Moo>Beastfolk weren't treated very well until a generation ago,
but now it's normal for them to be treated the same as
humans. Your ancestors worked hard for this to happen.

\n<Moo>Don't do anything to disgrace your family name, alright?
Chelsea. I'm speaking to you.
\n<Chelsea>Why are you suddenly throwing this at me?

\n<Moo>Hmm. Well, your head isn't very good. Not just not very
good, but actually quite bad. I apologize, but it wouldn't
be wrong to call you an idiot.

\n<Moo>When we first met, you were knocking down adventurers left
and right. You caused so much trouble that there was even a
subjugation request issued for you. It seems you just
couldn't help wanting to test your overwhelming power.

\n<Moo>"If you're going to punch something, punch monsters," I
said, and thus I recommended you become an adventurer. And
in the end, you ended up sticking with us.

\n<Moo>A brawler who's impulsive, hearty, and muscle-brained but
also honest and not a bad person. Somehow, you have a
strange charisma about you. Eventually, you get along with
everyone.

\n<Moo>At heart, you're kind and warm-hearted. Your cheerfulness
has helped... both Shion and myself. That's the kind of girl
you are.
\n<Chelsea>(I feel like I've been praised a lot. Ehehehe♥)

\n<Moo>(I should end on a compliment... That was close; I almost
went on a tirade. Being too honest is my flaw.)

\n<Moo>Me? I am the Holy Dragon Bahamut. You can call me Moo. That
might make you feel more attached? But let me make it clear,
I am nothing like a Pomeranian.

\n<Moo>Well... if I had to say... I'm something like Shion's...
guardian.

\n<Moo>Shion? Well, we'll get to that eventually. All will be
revealed in time.
